O’BRIEN BROTHERS, Inc., Owner of The Scow WESTERN LIGHT, Libelant-Appellee, v. GOODWIN-GALLAGHER SAND & GRAVEL CORPORATION, Respondent-Appellant. No. 246. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. Feb. 15, 1932. Maeklin, Brown, Lenahan & Speer, of New York City (Horace L. Cheyney, of New York City, of counsel), for appellant. Foley & Martin, of New York City (James A. Martin, of New York City, of counsel), for appellee.

Before MANTON, AUGUSTUS N. HAND, and CHASE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decree affirmed.
